<br>
K, onto the next issue.  Silyana was mine and Gonner's monk, Gonner is a good friend of mine and still is to this day.  He can verify everything I am going to say.  Anyway, after Silyana got a bit higher level, Gonner played her full time.  I had no problem with this, because Gonner was my friend and I wanted him to get more enjoyment out of the game and Gonner told me he was recently told &quot;hell no you cant apply to AD&quot; or something to that extent.  So Gonner played Silyana all the time.  I was happy playing my wizard and I was in AD where so many wonderful people are.  I had no problem with it.  I didn't even care who he gave the info to.<br>
<br>
So anyway, Gonner gives the info to Morb.  I didn't mind, because I was in Revered also, and I liked the hairy-footed little guy.  I saw Silyana online alot, and it was Morb, Gonner seemed to have went AFK for months.  Time went by, I didn't care at all that Morb was playing Silyana.  Anyway, one day I went to log on Silyana, I was curious how my monk was doing, and tired of casting spells, I wanted to punch stuff.  The info was changed.  So I logged into my wizard, and messaged Silyana.  Morb responded, told me it was him and everything, and the second I asked for the info, it seemed like I was put on ignore.  So I was not allowed to get the info for the account where I purchased the disks and powerleveled the character up, and twinked it up, and paid for it for months.  This made me a bit angry.  I always give people the benefit of the doubt.  I would just think, maybe he is busy, maybe he really can't answer me back, maybe he is LD.  So it was cold-sholdered for a couple weeks.  Eventually, Morb went AFk for a while too, so I had no way of contacting him.  And I wanted to play the monk really bad.  So I attempted the original password and it didn't work.  Had my friend call into customer service and gave him all of my EQ disks, and he had to do all this stuff.  So the GM restored the password, and I logged on finding out that the account had expired.  I fire the account back up and log in and start having fun.  Couple weeks later Morb messages me and that's where his argument begins.  I'm not sure where the fungi tunic went.  But I am absolutely certain about the first part of the story.<br>
<br>
I didn't care at all that Morb was playing Silyana.  I trusted Gonner and I trusted that he was responsible enough to trust someone responsible.  I only reacted in the way I did because Morb reused to give me access to my own monk.  I understand changing PW's on other people's accounts, maybe someone got a hold of it, or saw you typing it in.  But refusing the original owner of the character access is totally absurd.<br>
