Morb is loyal.<br>
<br>
IMO if both Xan and Morb agree the monk/fungi is a dead issue, he should be allowed to recruit.<br>
<br>
As for his frustration with AD, I feel it is valid, but a little misplaced.  Put yourself in his hairy feet for a second.  You put all your efforts into person after person trying to build a guild all the while those people swearing their loyalty to you just to have them leave once they gain lvl/gear.  If all the people who have passed through Revered would have stayed then there is no doubt IMO that Revered would be an AD rival this very day.  But things being what they are and people wanting to be part of what is 'The Best' at that particular second with no thought of the future and building your (the guild you belong to atm) into 'The Best' of tomorrow.  They forget their oaths of loyalty and move on to something bigger/better for their own good.  <br>
<br>
Lesson in point, It was AD's view of what 'could be' instead of what 'was' that allowed them to move from a small guild with dreams into the top guild on the server.<br>
<br>
Back to the subject, Morb is a good guy and a competent player and would bring more to AD than the average player. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bascension10244.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xanthala>xanthala</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pussycat Extraordinaire</span><br>  Posts: 356<br> <font color=#333333>(4/25/03 7:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://p075.ezboard.com/fascension10244frm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=438.topic&index=57>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: my 2cp</span><hr size=1> Yea its a dead issue.<br>
